HEADWORD: oeillade
<hw>oeil"lade`</hw>
<pr>(⟦etil⟧"y⟦adot⟧d`)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>oeillade</ets>, fr. <ets>oeel</ets> eye. See
<er>Eyelent</er>.]</ety> <def>A glance of the eye; an amorous
